	"description": "Why we need Concurrency\nOnce, there was a good old time when clock speed doubled every 18 months. This\nphenomenon was called Moore’s law. If a programmer’s program was not fast\nenough, they could wait, and soon computers would catch up.\n\nIt was too good to last, and it did not. CPU designers still kept up with\nMoore’s Law by adding more cores to computers.\n\nThis created a problem for programmers. In the new world, our programs will run\ntwice as fast every 18 months, but only if it is a parallel ",
